  "text": "The dashboard JSON model versioning and migration system lives entirely under `apps/dashboard/pkg/migration/`. The core architecture is: (1) `schemaversion/migrations.go` defines the schema version constants (MIN_VERSION=0, LATEST_VERSION=42), the `SchemaVersionMigrationFunc` type, `GetMigrations()` which maps version numbers to migration functions, and `GetSchemaVersion()` for reading the current version from dashboard JSON. (2) `migrate.go` contains the `migrator` struct singleton that orchestrates the full migration pipeline \u2014 applying frontend defaults, ensuring unique panel IDs, running the version-specific migration chain from V2 through V42, adding built-in annotations, and cleanup. (3) 41 individual version migration files (`v2.go` through `v42.go`) each implement field-level migration functions (e.g., V16 upgrades row-based layouts to grid layouts, V33/V36 handle datasource reference migrations). (4) Supporting utilities: `datasource_utils.go` (datasource name-to-ref conversion), `migration_utils.go` (helper functions), `errors.go` (migration error types), and `frontend_defaults.go` (applies DashboardModel/PanelModel constructor defaults before migrations run).",
